title: Where are they now? Kendall Knisley
text:
Dead End BBQ's Where are they Now?
Kendall Knisley
Alabama Huntsville, volleyball
Farragut High School
Now: Knisley, a 5-foot-10 senior middle blocker, has 221 total blocks and 589 kills in 107 career matches, including a career-best 94 blocks and 227 kills as a sophomore. She ranks third on the team in both blocks (28) and kills (102).
Then: The 2010 and 2011 all-PrepXtra selection helped Farragut to fifth place finishes at the state tournament as both a freshman (2008) and senior (2011). She was named District 4-AAA co-blocker of the year as a junior, and was named to the Region 2-AAA all-tournament team.
Chris Thomas covers high school sports. Follow him at twitter.com/PrepXtra
